name: Rena Rouge vol. 37 That big Color  edition
description: Rena Rouge vol. 37 That big Color edition is a full color, large format  version of vol. 37,  if you ever looked at a  blacklight poster and said man I sure do wish I had a book  that was this cool  and glowed.  Then this is the book for you!  measuring in at 10.5X15.75 in.  and bolted together with Seattle steel red studs this book is really weird  in every way possible.  and also dose weird stuff when you look at it  with those old 3-D glasses you know the kind, the red and blue ones.  not those stupid as new ones  they make you pay $2 extra for  at the picture show.  those things suck!  don't get those, but get this book, because it's cool.

name: Rena Rouge vol. 38
description: hot dog! more  tales of a girl and her big noodle worm.  In this volume we meet Satanic  sea mammals,  cigarette ash sky pirate hounds,  militaristic sheepdogs,  and a damn sky whale! vol. 38  is printed in black and white on ivory paper and  clocks in at around 26  pages. making it twice as long as vol. 37.

name: Rena Rouge vol. 37
description:
rena rouge vol. 37 chronicles the ever going adventures of Rena Rogue [Legally changed and observed by the state of New Illinois*] and her lindwrom Barnaby as they journey to deliver a goat to a respected client only to cactus armies, the tapeworm wizard, and a pooka witch. vol. 37 is 8.5x11in and is 16 pages of ink on paper with 12 of those pages being readable story! the cover is a two ink offset print on purple card stock. each copy will come with a sticker of the New Illinois  lindwrom department of transportation seal.   
*as noted in volume 38
